Khartoum, 4, Sep. (SUNA) - The Chief Justice, Professor Haidar Ahmed Dafalla, affirmed the strong relations linking Sudan to Kuwait, expressing keenness to boost them , further, in judiciary field. This came when the Chief Justice addressed the opening session of workshop of the joint Sudanese - Kuwait training session on the cross border crimes and money laundering which organized by joint committee of Sudanese Kuwaiti judiciary bodies. He appreciated the efforts of the Chairman of high council of judiciary in Kuwait , Advisor, , yousif Jasem, for boosting relations between the two countries.